task.summary: Created a basic shell for the Fibonacci CRUD API. This shell includes: - A router package that holds the Router and HandleFuncs. - A postgres package that creates the Postgres connection and handles the inserts, gets, updates, and deletions. - A model package that holds the Fibonacci schema.
- Updated variable and package names for clarification purposes - Added router package - Moved main.go and .env to root level

- Refactored application to use gorm for postgres related functionality due to having issues with the import: database/sql not properly reading in the connection string. - Switched router to use gin instead of gorilla/mux. - Updated model to account for gorm. - Moved routes to main for brevity.
- Added comments - Dockerized application (added Dockerfile and docker-compose.yml) - Set router to use port 8080
-Adding a Makefile to make running the application easier.
